cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.CV

The paper proposes a statistically motivated outlier removal algorithm for TDOA measurements, which can be applied in various fields such as acoustic source localization, sensor synchronization, radar, and remote sensing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a likely category as the paper deals with sensor arrays and proposes a method for outlier removal in TDOA measurements. 

Secondly, cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper uses statistical methods to identify spurious measurements within a set of TDOA/RD measurements. 

Thirdly, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be a relevant category as the paper deals with sensor arrays and proposes a method for outlier removal, which could be applied in networked systems. 

Fourthly, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper uses simulations to validate the proposed outlier removal algorithm. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with range differences and proposes a method for outlier removal, which could be applied in image processing and computer vision.
